                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.7111/282</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Rumanian Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davila</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-23">October 23,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of October ninth relative to the detention and arrest of your
                    chauffeur, Albert Amiaud, which took place on the evening of September thirtieth
                    between Providence and Westerly, Rhode Island.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that the contents of your note have been
                    forwarded to the Governor of Rhode Island asking that your request for
                    reimbursement of the amount your chauffeur was compelled to pay be given
                    consideration. Upon reply from the Governor I shall be pleased to communicate
                    with you further.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
